# sv_resolve_output_logical_types; VARCHAR fallback for DUCKDB_TYPE_INVALID
# inside try_infer_schema) are promoted to BinderException with the actual
# DuckDB error text plumbed through. CHANGELOG entry under `### Changed`
# documents the user-visible behaviour shift (D-16).
#
# Future assertions (Plan 11 populates):
#   B1: A semantic view whose FACTS or METRICS expression is deliberately
#       broken (e.g. references a nonexistent column) MUST raise a
#       `statement error` block whose tail contains the substring
#       "failed to infer column types" — confirms the new hard-error path
#       supplants the old silent fallback to a placeholder type.
#   B2: An existing valid `semantic_view(...)` query MUST still succeed —
#       confirms the promotion does not regress the happy path (the
#       LIMIT-0 probe should resolve types cleanly when the underlying
#       expression compiles).

require semantic_views

statement ok
LOAD semantic_views;

